Diagnosis.

Gonatocerus
(
Gonatocerus
) 
rivalis

is distinguished by the following combination. F6 of female antenna (
Fig. 51
) without mps and shorter than F5 or F7. Forewing (
Fig. 53
) 3.7–4.0x as long as wide, often with a more or less distinct brown apical spot; longest marginal seta 0.31–0.36x maximum wing width. Ovipositor (
Fig. 52
) 1.9–2.1x length of mesotibia and exserted by about 0.2x own length beyond apex of gaster.
